                <head>210. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> General Assembly approved Resolution 2961B
                    (XXVII) lowering the maximum contribution of any member state to ordinary <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> expenses to 25 percent on December 13, 1972, by a
                    vote of 81 in favor, 27 against, with 22 abstaining and 2 absent. (Yearbook of
                    the United Nations, 1972 (New York, 1975), pages 712 and 717)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
